<SLUG> BC-HUNKS-AZR </SLUG>
  
 BC-HUKS-AZR(a) 
 &HT;    BATTLE OF THE HUNKS: GIBSON VS. CLOONEY(a) 
 &HT;    (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)(a) 
 &HT;    By BILL MULLER(a) 
 &HT;    c.2000 The Arizona Republic(a) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   This week, Mel Gibson goes toe to toe with George Clooney in the
blockbuster fight of the summer - Gibson in (beginitalic)The
Patriot (enditalic)vs. Clooney in (beginitalic)The Perfect
Storm(enditalic).
</P>
<P>
   It's a box-office title bout that almost never came off.
</P>
<P>
   In fact, it nearly was Mel vs. Mel.
</P>
<P>
   Originally, (beginitalic)Storm(enditalic)'s producers wanted
Gibson to play the fishing boat captain whose small craft is
trapped in a horrific storm. But the studio balked at his asking
price, a reported $25 million. Besides, he was busy making his
Revolutionary War epic, (beginitalic)The Patriot(enditalic), also
known as (beginitalic)Braveheart With Muskets(enditalic).
</P>
<P>
   So, Warner Bros. hired Clooney, reportedly paying him about half
what Gibson wanted.
</P>
<P>
   With both movies opening this week ((beginitalic)Patriot
(enditalic)on Wednesday and (beginitalic)Perfect Storm
(enditalic)on Friday), it sets the stage for a pivotal battle
between Hollywood hunks.
</P>
<P>
   You have Gibson, the established star with an unbelievable track
record at the box office, against Clooney, an up-and-comer who has
experienced critical success ((beginitalic)Three Kings(enditalic))
but has yet to approach Gibson's numbers.
</P>
<P>
   The question is, can (beginitalic)The Perfect Storm
(enditalic)put Clooney in Gibson's league, or will the concept and
special effects swallow him whole, much like they did in
(beginitalic)Batman &AMP; Robin(enditalic)?
</P>
<P>
   The jury's still out, but this role should move Clooney up the
ladder.
</P>
<P>
   Gibson and Clooney aren't that different, at least in terms of
appeal. Both are handsome diablos, dominating those ubiquitous
``sexiest man'' lists. Although self-deprecating in person, they
play their parts broadly, almost winking at the camera with a Cary
Grant-type charm that makes audiences smile.
</P>
<P>
   They've paid their dues. Gibson, who at 44 is five years older,
first popped up in (beginitalic)Mad Max (enditalic)(1979), a
stylish film about cops and crooks in a brutal, futuristic
Australia. It led to two sequels, but Gibson didn't really make his
presence felt until (beginitalic)Lethal Weapon (enditalic)(1987),
teaming with Danny Glover as a sometimes-suicidal,
always-wisecracking maverick detective.
</P>
<P>
   The (beginitalic)Lethal Weapon (enditalic)series was enormously
successful at the box office, as even the wretched fourth
installment cracked the $100 million mark. In recent years, Gibson
has cranked out a succession of other hits, most notably
(beginitalic)Ransom (enditalic)and
(beginitalic)Braveheart(enditalic), the Scottish war epic that he
also directed.
</P>
<P>
   Clooney was raised in a show-biz family (his father is a host on
the American Movie Classics cable channel, and his aunt is jazz
singer Rosemary Clooney), but he was humbled early on.
</P>
<P>
   He did 13 failed television pilots and starred in an awful
B-movie, (beginitalic)Return of the Killer Tomatoes!(enditalic) He
finally struck pay dirt as Dr. Doug Ross on (beginitalic)ER,
(enditalic)the television series about a Chicago hospital.
</P>
<P>
   Springboarding off that success, Clooney has chosen his film
roles carefully, making the horror flick (beginitalic)From Dusk
Till Dawn (enditalic)(with Quentin Tarantino), the romantic comedy
(beginitalic)One Fine Day (enditalic)as well as (beginitalic)Batman
&AMP; Robin, The Peacemaker, Out of Sight (enditalic)and, last year,
(beginitalic)Three Kings(enditalic).
</P>
<P>
   The last movie, about three profiteering soldiers during the
Persian Gulf War, smacked of a breakthrough role for Clooney. You
got the idea that he was carrying the film rather than just playing
his part.
</P>
<P>
   Of course, Gibson has been doing that for a long time, hoisting
up light-scripted films such as (beginitalic)Conspiracy Theory
(enditalic)and (beginitalic)Payback(enditalic) and making them
legit in the process.
</P>
<P>
   This weekend, we get to see who comes out on top, as the
box-office champ meets the contender.
</P>
<P>
   May the best hunk win.
</P>
<P>
   $$$
</P>
