 &UR; WEBVAN _  &LR;  Webvan Group of Foster City, Calif., agreed to join
forces with HomeGrocer.com of Kirkland, Wash., Monday in a merger
of the No. 2 and No. 3 players in the Internet grocery business.
</P>
<P>
   The all-stock deal, which involves 138 million Webvan shares,
was valued at $1 billion at market close Monday. Webvan will
exchange 1.076 shares for each share of HomeGrocer. Webvan's stock
fell 16 percent to $7.31 yesterday, while HomeGrocer's declined 15
percent to close at $6.88.  &UR; BY CAROL EMERT &LR;
