<P>
   TECH-LYCOS (Undated) _ Lycos chief executive Bob Davis won't
bother to learn Spanish for his bid to dominate Latin America.
Instead, Davis has brought in a partner fluent in providing
Internet connections south of Texas, an arm of Spanish phone giant
Telefonica SA. The unit, Terra Networks, is purchasing Lycos for
$12.5 billion in stock, in a deal that promises to fundamentally
change the web portal. By Ross Kerber. 1850 words. PHOTO
</P>
<P>
   TECH-SYSTEMS (Undated) _ Consumers and investors have rebuked
companies sharply for lumbering online with poorly conceived
e-commerce sites. But a report says the designers and builders of
Web sites _ the Internet services and consulting firms that have
sprouted around the country _ share much of the blame. By Stephanie
Stoughton. 1075 words.
</P>
<P>
   TECH-SUBMARINE (Undated) _ Run silent. Run deep. Run wireless.
US Navy submarines, long-time models of sophisticated technology,
finally have plumbed the Internet. The first recorded e-mail from a
submerged sub, the USS Dolphin, was tapped out and transmitted
successfully to shore on the Friday before Memorial Day weekend. By
Robert Weisman. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   TECH-POLITICS (Palo Alto, Calif.) _ TechNet is trying to promote
political involvement by the techies in Silicon Valley. But for
many, politics and government remain alien realms. By Alex Pham.
</P>
<P>
   TECH-ROUNDUP (Undated) _ Trends in technology. By Ronald
Rosenberg.
</P>
<P>
   TECH-VENTURE (Boston) _ Can you trademark due diligence? One law
firm thinks so, and it's telling clients as much in its bid to
provide one-stop service for high-tech startups on the road to
venture funding. By Beth Healy. 660 words.
</P>
