<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MAKEUP-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;     SHADOWY, RETRO LOOK FOR FALL MAKEUP 
</HEADLINE>
   &HT;     (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 &HT;     By CYNTHIA ROBINS  
 &HT;     c.2000 San Francisco Examiner  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO _ Heads up, girls . . . the '50s have returned. At
least on the face.
</P>
<P>
   Makeup for fall is on the retro side, concentrating on elegantly
groomed and definitively sexy eyebrows, smoked-up eyes and
blood-red lips. Think: The Wicked Queen, Cruella De Vil, Joan
Crawford, Lisa Fossangrieves (photographer Irving Penn's
deliciously haute model wife whose face was the icon of the age).
</P>
<P>
   Yves Saint Laurent's collection is called Snapshot because of
its graphic imagery: squared off nails, the perfect match for the
Copyright Red lips; eyes fringed with dark lashes, lids softly
grayed down and nearly naked; loads of dark mascara.
</P>
<P>
   Calvin Klein's look is almost identical to YSL's but far more
pared down. Instead of heavily defined eyes, Calvin's lids are
nearly naked, slicked with very sheer tones of gray-beige and
barely coated with mascara _ only the top lid is lined. Lips are
the lightest of all the fall collections with a mocha and a beige;
however, Calvin's Merlot lipstick is as burgundy as its namesake.
</P>
<P>
   Jean and Jane Ford can always be counted on for an interesting
twist on a current trend. Their retro Fall 2000 color collection is
called Strictly Ballroom, a bounty of deeply satisfying,
outrageously shimmery lip and eye sparkles. Three
industrial-strength lip glosses injected with glimmer finish in
shades of bright red (Work That Skirt), mauve (Count the Beat) and
copper (Dip Me, Don't Drop Me). For eyes, the twins have
resurrected the powdered disco shadows of the '70s with gold
(Jitterbug), cherry burgundy (Swing) and sparkled anthracite
(Hustle). Three words of advice: Practice, practice, practice.
</P>
<P>
   Chanel's fall collection adheres to a silver standard _ that is,
silver sparkle on the eyes with deeply satisfying black lashes,
gemstone-hued lips in tones of burgundy (Pulsar), deep red
(Calypso) and fuchsia (Laser Pink) heated up with a dual compact of
ruby/blush pink gloss. Over all of it: Platinum Face Power which
wreathes the face in a halo of soft, moonstruck light.
</P>
<P>
   The lips have it with MAC's equally graphic Lady Danger
collection. You have a choice of reds in shades so deep, you could
drown in them: Underworld (blackened red), Miss Dish (deep cherry
red), Lady Danger (fiery orange red) and Russian Red (said to be
Madonna's favorite, a deep blue-red). Eyes may be lined with liquid
liner and emphasized with individually applied lashes in shades of
gold and black, but lids are fairly naked and shimmery with Pixel,
a pale, icy silver and Graphito, a gun-metal gray with dark silver
shimmer. If you're particularly gutsy, red around the eyes will not
make you look like a bunny, particularly if it's Flammable, a
glistening crimson. Believe it or not, it'll do wonders for your
eyes and reputation.
</P>
<P>
   Stay tuned for more makeup fashion for fall. New colors are
arriving every day.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
