<TEXT>
<P>
   Editors at publications outside the United States may find the
following stories from the New York Times News Service for
 &UR; WEDNESDAY, June 28,  &LR; of particular interest:
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL &LR;
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in `i' news category)
</P>
<P>
   CUBA-U.S. (Washington) _ After five hours of negotiations,
Republican leaders in the House of Representatives agreed early
Tuesday to allow sales of U.S.-grown food and medicine to Cuba,
thereby relaxing the sanctions that Washington invoked against the
communist regime in Havana 38 years ago. By Lizette Alvarez.
