<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT-ARTS
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-PATRIOT _ Movie review: ``The Patriot,'' filmed partially
in South Carolina with Mel Gibson as sort of Revolutionary
Braveheart. It's a movie made by Hollywood committee, at times
overtly bloodthirsty and overblown. There are a couple of moments
of cinematic beauty (especially a nighttime battle in a plantation
front-yard that's both beautiful to look at and frightening. Grade:
C+. (StMurray, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 27.
</P>
<P>
   SURVIVOR-SEQUEL _ CBS is already planning the sequel to mega-hot
hit ``Survivor,'' but Phil Kloer has some tongue-in-chek
suggestions on how a sequel might work. (Kloer, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   FOOD
</P>
<P>
   SANGRIA _ Sangria is not merely a quintessential summer
refresher. It also mocks snobbish wine rules that try to tell us we
should not drink cheap wine, we shouldn't mix wine with other stuff
and shouldn't ever pour it over ice. Sangria does all of those
things proudly, unabashedly, exuberantly. (Dayton Daily News). 20.
WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   SANGRIA-RECIPES _ Four Sangria recipes to go with main story.
(Dayton Daily News). 15.
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS
</P>
<P>
   TENNIS
</P>
<P>
   TEN-WIMBLEDON-AGASSI _ WIMBLEDON _ Andre Agassi makes his debut
at Wimbledon vs. Taylor Dent. (Clarke, Palm Beach Post). 18.
</P>
<P>
   NBA DRAFT
</P>
<P>
   BKN-DRAFT-MAIN _ ATLANTA _ Overall advance of NBA Draft. The New
Jersey Nets are expected to take Kenyon Martin of Cincinnati with
the No. 1 overall choice. Iowa State forward Marcus Fizer and Texas
center Chris Mihm are also expected to be among those selected
early in the first round. Orlando has three of the top 13 picks
