Attorney General Janet Reno refuses to say whether she will appoint
a special counsel to investigate Vice President Al Gore's
fund-raising activities in 1996. Last week, Sen. Arlen Specter,
R-Pa., who has been holding hearings into campaign finance abuses,
announced that the head of the Justice Department's campaign
finance unit had recommended such a special investigation of the
vice president. By MARK HELM. Story will also be filed in the
POLITICAL NEWS (``p'') category.
