announces a major recruiting initiative to boost the service's
sagging ranks. Recruiting troops has been difficult because of the
robust economy over the last several years, especially for the
Army, which fell 6,300 short of its achieving its target of 74,500
new soldiers last year. By ERIC ROSENBERG.
