<P>
   CYC-LANCE _ Even though he's the Tour de France champion and
spends at least six months in France, France hasn't embraced Lance
Armstrong. He is in position to complete a miracle year when he
begins defense of his tour de france title Saturday. The road back
has been intriguing. The upside has been money, exposure and hero
stature. On the flip side, there're still a question about him
winning against a weak field in 1999, a concussion he had in May
and is he in shape enough to handle the tour and the Olympics.
Developing. (Halliburton, Austin American-Statesman). 30.
