   WORLDCOM-SPRINT (Undated) _ The Justice Department on Tuesday
set a limit on the telecommunications industry's headlong
consolidation as it moved to block Worldcom Inc.'s proposed $115
billion acquisition of the Sprint Corp. amid concerns that the
combined company would stifle competition in the Internet and
long-distance telephone industries. The deal is the biggest that
the Justice Department has tried to block. By Seth Schiesel and
David Leonhardt.
</P>
<P>
   ACCOUNTING-MARKETPLACE (Undated) _ The Securities and Exchange
Commission on Tuesday proposed new rules to tighten standards on
what other services accounting firms can sell to companies whose
books they audit. The proposal immediately ran into criticism from
some accounting firms, but gained support from others. By Floyd
Norris.
</P>
