<P>
   SCI-AFRICA-AIDS (Undated) _ An estimated 19 million people have
been killed and a further 34 million infected _ 5 million last year
_ by the AIDS virus, which is wreaking social and economic
devastation in the most stricken African nations. A U.N. report
paints an almost unremittingly grim picture; in some countries in
southern Africa, it predicts, half or more of people now under 15
will succumb to the disease. By Lawrence K. Altman.
</P>
