<P>
   NATALIE'S FRESH VEGETABLE POTATO SALAD VINAIGRETTE &QL; 
2 pounds red OR white potatoes, cooked until tender, chilled and
cut into 1-inch pieces (leave skins on) &QL; 
1 1/2 cups chopped hot house cucumbers &QL; 
2 cups diced tomatoes (squeeze out as much juice as possible before
cutting up) &QL; 
3 tablespoons drained capers &QL; 
2/3 cup diced pitted ripe olive OR kalamata olives &QL; 
1/3 cup chopped fresh basil &QL; 
1/3 cup extra-virgin olive oil &QL; 
1/4 to 1/3 cup red wine vinegar &QL; 
3/4 teaspoon garlic pepper &QL; 
1/4 teaspoon seasoned salt &QL;
</P>
<P>
   In a medium bowl, mix together potatoes, cucumbers, tomatoes,
capers and olives. Add remaining ingredients and mix gently until
well mixed. Serve immediately or chill until serving time. Makes 6
or more servings. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   CURRIED POTATO SALAD &QL; 
2 pounds red OR white potatoes, cooked until tender, chilled and
cut into 1-inch pieces &QL; 
1/2 cup chopped green onions &QL; 
1/4 cup golden raisins OR diced dried apricots &QL; 
1/2 cup chopped red bell pepper &QL; 
1 1/2 cups plain non-fat yogurt &QL; 
1 tablespoon curry powder &QL; 
2 to 3 tablespoons mango chutney &QL; 
2 tablespoons white OR red wine vinegar &QL; 
1/4 teaspoon seasoned salt &QL; 
1/4 teaspoon pepper &QL; 
2 cups diced cooked chicken (optional) &QL; 
1/4 cup chopped OR sliced almonds (optional) &QL; 
In a large bowl, combine potatoes, green onions, raisins and red
pepper.
</P>
<P>
   In a small bowl, mix together yogurt, curry powder, chutney,
vinegar, salt and pepper until well blended. Add to potato mixture,
tossing gently until evenly mixed. Stir in chicken, if desired.
Serve immediately or refrigerate until serving time. Sprinkle with
almonds just before serving. Makes 6 or more servings. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   HERBED POTATO SALAD WITH &QL; 
LEMON-OLIVE OIL DRESSING &QL; 
2 pounds red-skinned potatoes, peeled and cut into 1-inch pieces &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
1/4 cup extra-virgin olive oil &QL; 
1/2 cup finely chopped red onion &QL; 
1/2 cup finely chopped red bell pepper &QL; 
1/4 cup fresh lemon juice &QL; 
3 tablespoons chopped fresh oregano &QL; 
2 tablespoons chopped fresh mint &QL; 
2 teaspoons salt &QL; 
3/4 teaspoon ground black pepper &QL; 
Steam potatoes just until tender, about 10 minutes. Transfer
potatoes to a large bowl.
</P>
<P>
   Add oil to potatoes, toss to coat. Mix in red onion, bell
pepper, lemon juice, oregano, mint, salt and pepper. (Can be made 4
hours ahead. Cover; chill. Let stand at room temperature 1 hour
before serving). Makes 6 servings.
</P>
<P>
   From Bon Appetit June 2000 issue &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ALL-AMERICAN POTATO SALAD &QL; 
4 pounds large red potatoes &QL; 
Water &QL; 
1/2 cup cider vinegar &QL; 
3 tablespoons vegetable oil &QL; 
1 1/2 teaspoons salt &QL; 
3/4 teaspoon freshly ground pepper &QL; 
1 1/2 cups mayonnaise &QL; 
1/2 cup milk &QL; 
1 tablespoon Dijon mustard &QL; 
3 large celery ribs, chopped &QL; 
1/2 cup finely chopped red onion &QL; 
8 slices bacon, cooked until crisp and crumbled (optional) &QL; 
2 tablespoons chopped parsley &QL; 
4 hard-cooked eggs, quartered (optional) &QL; 
Parsley sprigs for garnish &QL; 
In a large saucepan or Dutch oven, cover potatoes with water. Bring
to a boil, reduce heat to medium, and cook until potatoes are
tender when pierced with a sharp knife, 25 to 30 minutes. Drain
into a colander.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, in a large bowl, whisk vinegar, oil, salt and pepper
until blended. Peel potatoes when cool enough to handle but still
warm, and cut into 3/4-inch cubes. Add warm potatoes to dressing
and stir gently to coat. Let cool to room temperature.
</P>
<P>
   In a small bowl, whisk mayonnaise, milk and mustard until
blended. Pour over potatoes. Add celery, red onion, bacon and
chopped parsley. Stir gently to mix. Cover and refrigerate at least
4 hours or overnight. &QL; 
Before serving, garnish with egg quarters and parsley sprigs. Makes
12 to 16 servings.
</P>
<P>
   From ``365 All-American Favorites,'' by Sarah Reynolds, Harper
Collins &QL;
</P>
