<SLUG> BC-TRIVIA-Q&AMP;A-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THE LAST DAYS AND SONGS OF BING CROSBY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: I understand that shortly before his death, Bing Crosby
recorded a song. What was it?
</P>
<P>
   _ A.R.P., Auburn, Mass.
</P>
<P>
   A: In the weeks before he died of a heart attack on Oct. 14,
1977, Crosby recorded two projects that were released as albums.
</P>
<P>
   From Sept. 12 to 14, Crosby recorded the album ``Seasons'' with
the Pete Moore Orchestra. The 12 songs all have seasonal themes,
including ``Sleigh Ride'' and a reprisal of his 1934 No. 1 hit,
``June in January.''
</P>
<P>
   On Oct. 11, Crosby was a guest on a BBC Radio program where he
sang eight songs with the Gordon Rose Orchesta, ending with the
song ``Once in a While.'' This was released as an album, ``Bing:
The Final Chapter.''
</P>
<P>
   After the 1977 deaths of Crosby and Elvis Presley, the record
industry delayed 500 albums and manufactured 4 million records a
day to keep up with the demand for their music, The New York Times
reported.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where can I write to Detroit Tiger Juan Gonzalez?
</P>
<P>
   _ M.F., Euless, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: Write to Gonzalez or any other player for the team in care of
the Detroit Tigers, 2100 Woodward Ave., Detroit, MI 48201.
</P>
<P>
   You might want to hurry with your letter. The Tigers are
reportedly talking with the New York Yankees about trading
Gonzalez, who becomes a free agent after this season.
</P>
<P>
   Gonzalez, 30, is a two-time American League most valuable
player. He was traded to Detroit by the Texas Rangers in the
off-season in a nine-player deal.
</P>
<P>
   Q: How would I go about getting a videotape from the History
Channel?
</P>
<P>
   _ B.J.W., Arlington, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: A&AMP;E Television sends out a World of A&AMP;E Catalog that includes
videotapes from the History Channel, A&AMP;E and the new Biography
Channel.
</P>
<P>
   To request a catalog, call (888) 423-1212 or visit the Web site
store.aetv.com.
</P>
<P>
   Among the History Channel shows offered on video are ``History
Undercover,'' ``America at War,'' ``Sea Tales'' and ``20th Century
with Mike Wallace.''
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
