<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs on
Wednesday, June 28, and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact William Toren at the Daily News, (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   LACOUNTY-BAILOUT (Los Angeles) _ The massive Los Angeles County
health care system received a reprieve when state and federal
officials granted a one-time $1.2 billion Medicaid waiver that will
keep services for more than 3 million residents solvent. By Troy
Anderson. (Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California
state news files.)
</P>
<P>
   ACTORS-STRIKE (Los Angeles) _ The vast and largely untapped
Internet is stalling talks between actors unions and advertisers to
end a strike now entering its ninth week. Actors want some
guarantee of payment on ads displayed on the Internet, something
advertisers refuse to do. By Dominic Berbeo. (Will move in the
``a'' national and ``n'' California state news files.)
</P>
