is difficult to imagine Turkey without raki. More than simply the
national drink, it is a potent, anise-flavored distillation of the
Turkish soul. It accompanies much of the best after-dark
conversation and is woven inextricably into the country's social
fabric. In restaurants in Istanbul and elsewhere in Turkey, a toast
with raki is part of the meal. (Staton R. Winter/The New York
