   (NYT1) HAVANA -- June 27, 2000 -- CUBA-U.S. -- Congressional
critics of Fidel Castro reached agreement with farm-state House
members early Tuesday to allow direct sales of U.S. food to Cuba
for the first time in nearly four decades. Cubans shopped at a
local market in March where food is bountiful but prices are
prohibitive to the average Cuban. (David Tulis/The Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
