<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   HOUSE-CUBA (Washington) _ Congressional leaders agree to permit
exports of food and medicine to Cuba for the first time in almost
40 years, a victory for farm-state lawmakers who fought Republican
leaders and conservatives opposed to deviating from the
longstanding embargo. GREG McDONALD.
</P>
<P>
   RENO-GORE (Washington) _ Warning against investigations
conducted ``in headlines,'' Attorney General Janet Reno refuses to
say whether she will appoint a special counsel to investigate Vice
President Al Gore's 1996 fund-raising activities. Resisting calls
by Republican senators for a special counsel in Gore's case, Reno
says that publicly discussing it could taint the probe. By MARK
HELM. (Already filed; also filed in ``p'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   ARMY-RECRUITING (Washington) _ Army Secretary Louis Caldera
announces a major recruiting drive to boost the service's sagging
ranks by
</P>
<P>
   embarking on a $380 million advertising campaign, geared in
large
</P>
<P>
   part toward attracting minorities. By ERIC ROSENBERG. (Already
filed.)
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MOUSE-GENOME (Albany, N.Y.) _ With scientists making astonishing
breakthroughs in understanding the genetic makeup of humans,
researchers also are keeping an eye on the mapping of the mouse
genome. A genetic map of the most widely used lab animal in the
world would give researchers a way to manipulate and interpret
scientific findings and aid in the understanding of human diseases.
By SYLVIA WOOD. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ We are, as we have always known,
what we eat. But everyone is always trying to lose weight. Newsweek
moans this week that our kids are too fat. People magazine has just
examined the proliferating celebrity diets. But now there is a
backlash. Nutritionists and others are complaining that those bags
of bones in the women's magazines and on TV are just too darn thin.
By MARIANNE MEANS. (Already filed.)
</P>
