</P>
<P>
   WORLDCOM-SPRINT (Undated) _ The Justice Department seeks to curb
the headlong consolidation of the telecommunications industry by
moving to block WorldCom Inc.'s proposed $115 billion acquisition
of Sprint Corp. In seeking an injunction against the deal in
federal court, the Justice Department cites concerns that the
combined company would stifle competition on the Internet and in
the long-distance telephone industry. By Seth Schiesel and David
Leonhardt. (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in ``f'' news file.)
1,500 words.
