everything, and when it came to timing, the opponents of the
Miranda decision who finally managed to push the Supreme Court into
revisiting the case after 34 years turned out to have been
spectacularly unlucky. A news analysis by Linda Greenhouse.
(Scheduled to move by 8:15 p.m. ET in ``w'' news file.) 1,000
