<P>
   &UR; POKERFACE-PUTIN-ECONOMIST &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Three months after Vladimir Putin won Russia's presidency, some
ugly things have been happening in his benighted country. The new
man, a former KGB officer, has been cracking his whip. He has
sounded belligerent towards several of Russia's former vassal
states on its rim, and shows little sign of softening towards
Chechnya, the rebel republic devastated at his command. Things may
yet change but, for the time being at least, Putin remains on
probation. &QL;
