<P>
   HARARE_ In a free and fair election, the ruling party of
Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe would stand no chance. His
government is violent, corrupt, incompetent and detested. But his
ZANU enjoys the advantages of incumbency. Yet despite that _ and a
vicious campaign of intimidation and killings _ the ruling party
could still lose its majority in this weekend's election. &QL;
