   BEIRUT _ When is a border less than a border? When it is blue.
So, at least, runs the contention of the United Nations officials
trying to confirm the Israeli army's retreat from south Lebanon.
They have invented a new, blue ``withdrawal line'' where it thinks
the Lebanese border should run. But the Lebanese government, which
already has to cope with green, red, black and purple lines left
behind by the country's civil war, is reluctant to add another
shade to the spectrum. It argues that the new boundary leaves
several chunks of Lebanese territory inside Israel. &QL;
